===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# The act or process of [[absorbing]] or of being [[absorbed]] as,
## {{lb|en|obsolete}} engulfing; swallowing up, as of bodies or land. {{defdate|Attested from the late 16<sup>th</sup> century until the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=9}}</ref>
## [[assimilation]]; incorporation. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
##: ''the '''absorption''' of a smaller tribe into a larger''
##: ''the '''absorption''' of bodies in a [[whirlpool]]''
## {{lb|en|chemistry|physics}} the [[imbibing]] or [[reception]] by [[molecular]] or chemical action, of [[radiant]] [[energy]]; the process of being [[neutron]]s being absorbed by the [[nucleus]]; [[interception]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
##: ''the '''absorption''' of light, heat, electricity, etc.''
## {{lb|en|meteorology}} The process in which [[incident]] radiant energy is retained by a substance (such as an [[air mass]]) by conversion to some other form of energy (such as [[heat]]).
## {{lb|en|physiology}} in living organisms, the process by which the materials of growth and [[nutrition]] are absorbed and conveyed to the [[tissue]]s and [[organ]]s; taking in by various means, such as by [[osmosis]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# Entire [[engrossment]] or occupation of the mind. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: '''''absorption''' in some employment''
# Mental assimilation. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 20<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|electrical engineering}} The retaining of electrical energy for a short time after it has been introduced to the [[dielectric]].

